==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Cyrenian
<hw>Cy*re"ni*an</hw> <pr>(s?-r?"n?-⟦ait⟧n)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos>
<def>Pertaining to Cyrene, in Africa; Cyrenaic.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Cyrenian</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Cyrenian
<hw>Cy*re"ni*an</hw>, <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>A native or
inhabitant of Cyrene.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>One of a school of philosophers, established at
Cyrene by Aristippus, a disciple of Socrates. Their doctrines were
nearly the same as those of the Epicureans.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Cyriologic</ent>⟦br⟧
